            <sentence id="3.3">1 open firefox to a page with a combo box</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">2 put it on the secondary display</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">3 position the combo box on the screen such that it has too many items to fit</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.6">4 drop down the box</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.7">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.8">the drop down box gets cut off</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Expected Results:  
shortened the box to fit within the viewable screen, or opened it in the other
direction (up).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
